  "reasoning": "The article reports kinetic studies for CuS nanoclusters (NCs) acting as peroxidase‑like (POD), catalase‑like (CAT) and ascorbic‑acid‑oxidase‑like (AAO) nanozymes. For the POD activity two kinetic tracks are described: (i) TMB is the variable substrate while H₂O₂ is kept constant (reaction type TMB+H₂O₂) and (ii) H₂O₂ is the variable substrate while TMB is kept constant (reaction type H₂O₂+TMB). The reported Michaelis‑Menten constants (Kₘ) and maximum rates (Vₘₐₓ) for each track are extracted. The CAT activity is characterized by varying H₂O₂ concentration (single substrate) and its kinetic parameters are also extracted. The AAO activity is characterized by varying ascorbic acid (AA) concentration, providing its kinetic parameters. All other experimental conditions (pH, temperature, buffer, nanoparticle size, surface coating) are captured where reported. Each experiment is represented as an independent object following the NanozymeExtractionOutput schema."
